-- Japanese Bought Net 378.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2012-11-14T23:51:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-14/japanese-bought-net-378-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Nov. 9 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 378.4 billion yen ($4.7 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 38.9 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 4.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 335.4 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 309.1 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 79 billion yen in stocks, and bought 672.7 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 902.8
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
